title: Winnie Harlow sizzles in snakeskin coat and alligator boots at opening of Nordstrom flagship store
text:
She recently signed with LA-based talent agency CAA that represents some of Hollywood's biggest stars.

And on Tuesday night, model Winnie Harlow was among the famous faces who walked the red carpet at the star-studded opening for the new Nordstrom flagship store in New York.

The 25-year-old Canadian made quite an entrance in a brown snakeskin trench coat and diamond necklace.

Posed: Model Winnie Harlow was among the famous faces who walked the red carpet at the star-studded opening for the new Nordstrom flagship store in New York City on Tuesday night

Harlow wore the coat unbuttoned but loosely tied with the sash so as to reveal her black romper bodysuit.

The leggy model added a pair of thigh-high black alligator boots and carried a Louis Vuitton purse.

Her long hair was loose and she accessorized with large hoop earrings and gold-framed sunglasses.

Wild: The 25-year-old Canadian made quite an entrance in a brown snakeskin trench coat over a black romper bodysuit with thigh-high black alligator boots

Bling: Her long hair was loose and she accessorized with a diamond necklace, large hoop earrings and gold-framed sunglasses

The new Nordstrom department store is located at 57th and Broadway in Manhattan and spans more than 300,000 square feet over seven floors.

In addition to men and women's clothing, shoes and accessories, the Nordstrom will also offer beauty items, kids items and home goods.

The store boasts several restaurants and bars as well as original artwork.
